c: 6
v: 145
t: "Say, \"I do not find in the Revelation given to me, any food that is prohibited for one who wishes to eat except: Carrion (dead meat), running blood as against organ meats, the flesh of swine for it is disapproved, or anything (not just meat) which, in disobedience, has been dedicated to other than Allah.\" If one is forced by dire need without being deliberate and without transgressing, your Lord is Forgiving, Merciful."